hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: How long have you lived here? peninsula pharmacy ocean park wa Hanns was a tough interrogator with a burning vengeance. It is not difficult to understand why. At Belsen he wrote about the “dead bodies walking about, dead bodies lying about, people who thought they were alive and they weren’t,” a vivid summary of the hell the camps had become. Hanns represented a decent and more tolerant Germany and was willing to fight alongside Germany’s enemies to see his country restored.
